Burger King still corners the market with their Whopper. you really can have it your way. They have great ice cream shakes, but I have to tell you I have never tried the Lucky Charms Shake. It is a little too over-the-top for me. Their chicken fries are a nice little snack of protein when you don't want much. Their Icees are also really good, they have two flavors: Coke and Cherry. They carry Coke products for their soft drinks. Currently they have a special for a mix and match of Whoppers, chicken sandwiches, and one other item. You get two for $8 and then can add fries and a drink on top of that. When you go in for a visit, don't forget to do the survey. It will give you a free Whopper the next time you go in. Bb  Always check your order  before you leave the window. I'm not sure why they can't get their orders right 100% of the time, but they do make mistakes. They are also having a special with two croissandwiches with meat for $5. You can't beat their prices, combined with the excellent quality!!
